Description: Force keyboard focus when raising a window that demands attention.
 .
 WindowAttentionTracker previously called activate_with_focus() with
 display.get_current_time(), which returns the most recent X event
 timestamp. When the currently focused window's _NET_WM_USER_TIME equals
 that timestamp (e.g. the user was just typing in it), mutter's
 focus-steal prevention denies the activation and the window is raised
 but never receives keyboard focus. The result: the new window appears
 on top, but keypresses still go to the previous window.
 .
 Use get_current_time_roundtrip() to obtain a fresh server timestamp
 strictly newer than any prior input event, so the activation passes
 mutter's focus-steal check.
--- gala-8.5.1+r3055+pkg132~ubuntu8.1.orig/src/WindowAttentionTracker.vala
+++ gala-8.5.1+r3055+pkg132~ubuntu8.1/src/WindowAttentionTracker.vala
@@ -10,7 +10,8 @@
     }
 
     private static void on_window_demands_attention (Meta.Window window) {
+        var timestamp = window.display.get_current_time_roundtrip ();
         window.raise ();
-        window.get_workspace ().activate_with_focus (window, window.display.get_current_time ());
+        window.get_workspace ().activate_with_focus (window, timestamp);
     }
 }
